         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">30/3/87 ¶  ¶ It is delightful to contemplate, dear Dr Ramsay, that through your and your kind brothers and nephews action, ¶  we shall become acquainted with the plants of the remotest N.W. of N.SW. L...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.03.30b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">30/3/87</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is delightful to contemplate, dear Dr Ramsay, that through your and your kind brothers and nephews action,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>James Ramsay and his son Edward Lord Ramsay.</p>
               </note> we shall become acquainted with the plants of the remotest N.W. of N.SW. Let him particularly attend to the minutest annuals in spring also and to all sorts of Saltbushes. I should like much to know the northern boundary of the Quandong. I can send you a root of that marvellous perennial grass Vide "Select plants"<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Vide "Select plants<seg style="font-style: italic; ">" is a marginal note with its position marked by an asterisk. The current edition was B85.12.03</seg>.</p>
               </note>
               <name key="Panicum%20spectabile">Panicum spectabile</name> for your brother now at the cool season.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What do you intend to do with regard to Forbes? I have just a telegram from him, quite unexpectedly, that he is coming south.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Telegram not found.</p>
               </note> He has not communicated with me for a year or more.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mt Seaview is the one put down of the map as 6000' high on the Hastings River.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Both NSW; see M to E. Ramsay, 24 March 1887.</p>
               </note> This measurement is surely overrated. It stands in round numbers thus on the map for 30 years! Still it is very <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">high</hi>
               </seg> and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">isolated</hi>
               </seg>, but now very accessible thus it is sure to have <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">new</hi>
               </seg> plants in the higher regions and of course also some peculiar fishes in the rivulets, land insects &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Panicum%20spectabile">Panicum spectabile</name>
            </p>
